      "type": "strategy",
      "content": "This task is a combination of extraction (pulling out filing numbers, dates, parties, and collateral descriptions), comparison/reconciliation (cross-referencing the Ohio SOS search certificates and Summit County search with individual UCC filings to ensure completeness and identify discrepancies), issue-flagging (identifying active liens, judgment liens, tax liens, and false positives that affect the senior secured status of the proposed lender), and drafting (synthesizing these findings into a structured lien search summary report). The approach will involve creating a master lien matrix mapping each entity to its active encumbrances, identifying priority conflicts, and recommending specific payoff or termination actions.",
